#- 




§lHaven: A Home for All§r
§oBy EnigmaticHobo
#- Once upon a time on the outskirts of the Far West near the remains of the runined Aristopolis and the fledgling city of The Central came a new sanctuary for both the lost and the found of the world, Haven. Haven, was built upon the hopes that both
#- griefers and non-griefers, communists and capitalists anarchists and socialists, atheists and theists, could all live under the same roof in peace and that judgement would only be rendered upon those that attempted to
#- break that peace. Haven provides sanctuary for the poor and the rich alike. All are accepted as long as they keep the oath of pure neutrality at all times. Haven relys on both it's own strength and that of both friendly Civilizations, organizations,
#- and all manner of individuals to help keep the peace within Haven. To this end Haven has hosted notorious griefers and made a strategtic alliance with the LSIF and will ally with any person or group that wishes to help keep Haven powerful and a santuary
#- for ALL.
#- This is the original work of EnigmaticHobo. It has been transcribed from Bookworm over to Book and Quill by SomethingSaucy for the benefit of the Citadel and all of Civcraft.
#- 